  "original_title": "Table IMF staff level agreement in Parliament: Harsha tells President",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Table IMF staff level agreement in Parliament: Harsha tells President",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Samagi Jana Balawegaya (SJB) MP and Chairman of Public Finance Committee Dr. Harsha de Silva today requested President Ranil Wickremesinghe to table the staff level agreement with IMF before Parliament on Tuesday.",
        "\"I will use my powers as Chairman of Public Finance Committee and get the document out, if President fails to do so on that day,\" Dr. de Silva said during a media conference today.",
        "\"We need to know what the government had agreed to do it in accordance with the staff level agreement. We understand that the government will have to get into agreement with creditors on restructuring debts. All citizens will be affected if domestic debt is to be restructured. The press release of IMF says that Sri Lanka will have to convert the capital account deficit into a surplus by 2025. This could result in huge tax regime and expenditure cuts,\" he said.",
        "\"Also we need to know the new legal structures which the President is going to introduce to curb correlation as well,\" he added. (Yohan Perera)"
      ],
